text: Kim Jung-mi (born 28 September 1975) is a South Korean sport shooter who competed in the 1996 Summer Olympics and in the 2004 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1975 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean female sport shooters Category:ISSF rifle shooters Category:Olympic shooters of South Korea Category:Shooters at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:Shooters at the 2004 Summer Olympics Category:Shooters at the 1998 Asian Games Category:Shooters at the 2002 Asian Games Category:Shooters at the 2010 Asian Games Category:Asian Games medalists in shooting Category:Asian Games gold medalists for South Korea Category:Asian Games silver medalists for South Korea Category:Medalists at the 1998 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 2002 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 2010 Asian Games
title: Kim Jung-mi
